# .trivyignore — Trivy vulnerability exceptions
#
# This file lists CVEs that are accepted risks for this project.
# Each entry is documented with the reason for acceptance.
#
# Policy: Only CVEs in OS base packages that cannot be remediated
# at the application layer are listed here. All Python/Node package
# CVEs must be fixed by upgrading dependencies, not listed here.
#
# OS base-image CVEs (python:3.12-slim / node:20-alpine):
# These come from the upstream base images (Debian 13 / Alpine).
# We cannot patch them at the application layer — we must wait for
# the base image maintainers to release a fix, then rebuild.
# We run `ignore-unfixed: true` in Trivy to suppress truly unfixed ones.
# Any that are listed below have been reviewed and accepted as low-risk
# in the context of this application (no direct exposure, mitigated by
# network isolation, non-root container user, and named Docker network).
#
# To identify new CVEs: download the SARIF artifact from the CI run
# and review trivy-api.sarif / trivy-worker.sarif / trivy-frontend.sarif

# Debian 13 (Bookworm/Trixie) stdlib CVEs — no fix available upstream
# Add specific CVE IDs here after reviewing the SARIF artifact, e.g.:
# CVE-XXXX-XXXXX
